migration
    once you create a new column in the customers model, you have to migrate using the migration command
        php artisan migrate
    you'll have to roll back the existing changes and then migrate the table again. this clears all changes made to the      database i.e this is just for practice
        php artisan migrate:rollback

yield
    this is used to partition views so that different sections of a view can be stored in different files
    go through layout for more details
to store your javascript files
    go to app.blade.php, under the scripts tags, add yours
to store your css files
    go to app.blade.php, under the styles tags, add yours